<div><h3>PHIL 1500 - Philsophy of Religion </h3>  <p><hr>A philosophical inquiry into the questions that lie at the center of religion: does God exist?  Is there a soul, and is it immortal?  Are miracles possible?  What is the relationship between faith and reason?  Is the reality of evil compatible with the existence of a good God?</p>

<p>This class is not a typical &#8220;religion&#8221; class.  We together will delve into the many questions that come to mind when we think of why we do what we do in the name of  &#8220;god/God&#8221; and the driving force behind the notion of faith. <br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> varies<br><br></p></div>		</td>
